# Documentation requirements by type — mandatory

## Public API (interfaces / public classes)
- Interface KDoc:
  - class-level KDoc: role/purpose
  - each method: purpose + `@param` + `@return`
- For public (non-internal) classes, provide class-level KDoc that clarifies concrete behavior and intended usage.

## Component / wiring classes (`*Component`, `*Module`)
- Every wiring component/module must have class-level KDoc describing:
  - what dependencies it requires (constructor parameters)
  - what it provides (public properties/functions)
  - any initialization contract (e.g. “must call `init()` before using `appErrorParser`”)
- Aggregate/wiring modules should clearly state which submodules they include/coordinate.

## Error models (sealed error hierarchies implementing `AppError`)
- For each sealed hierarchy (e.g. `CommonError`, `SecurityError`, `UserError`):
  - class-level KDoc: purpose + meaning of `code`, `args`, and `isRetryable`
  - each variant:
    - short description of when it happens
    - `@param` for ctor params (if any)
    - describe `args` usage:
      - what keys can appear in `args`
      - whether values are safe for user display and/or logging

## Value classes / identifier wrappers (`@JvmInline value class`)
- For value classes that wrap UUID/parseable identifiers and cross network/storage/serialization boundaries:
  - provide `asHexDashString()` instance method
  - provide `companion object fun generate()`
  - provide parsing extensions following the project naming:
    - `String.toXxxOrNull()` when invalid input should be handled gracefully
    - `String.toXxxOrThrow()` when invalid input must be treated as a programming/contract violation
- If a value class is intentionally “opaque” (e.g. tokens not parsed from string), do not add parsing extensions; still document its invariants/purpose.

## Localization-aware types
- Any class that maps error codes to localized strings (i.e. implementations of `AppErrorParser`) must have KDoc explaining:
  - what codes it handles
  - what it returns for unknown/unmapped codes (delegate to `CommonErrorParser`).

## KMP/UI state models
- For UI state sealed interfaces/classes used by screens (e.g. `*ScreenState`):
  - provide KDoc on the root sealed type to explain the lifecycle/meaning of states
  - each state variant should clarify what the UI should display/do.
